<p><b>When was Don Camillo written?</b> Don Camillo's exploits were first published in the Italian magazine Candido in the late 1940s.</p>
<p><b>What does Peppone mean?</b> Don Camillo is constantly at odds with the Communist mayor, Giuseppe Bottazzi, better known as Peppone (meaning, roughly, 'Big Joe') and is also on very close terms with the crucifix in his town church.</p>
<p><b>Who is the mayor of Don Camillo?</b> In Don Camillo's Little World, where the Cold War is fought on the very doorstep of life, the hot-headed Catholic priest and the equally pugnacious Communist mayor, Peppone, confront one another in riotous and often hilarious manner.</p>